text: Tuolumne County (), officially the County of Tuolumne, is a county in the U.S. state of California. As of the 2020 census, the population was 55,620. The county seat and only incorporated city is Sonora. The county is in the Sierra Nevada region. The northern half of Yosemite National Park is in the eastern part of this county. Tuolumne County was founded in 1850. == References == Category:1850 establishments in California
title: Tuolumne County, California
